  "text": "We note here that, in order to compare AFM images produced by the asymmetric model and the symmetric model quantitatively, we use the normalized product correlation between the trace and retrace image, which is calculated by [CITATION_1] : where 0<R<1 is the normalized product correlation, and x t and x r are the gray value matrix of trace and retrace image, respectively. The normalized product correlation is often used to describe the similarity between two images. A bigger normalized product correlation means the two images are more similar, where R = 1 means the two images are exactly the same.",
